22 Aug 2009 03:28






This shows promise, but besides the already-mentioned blandness, I think a major problem with it is that it's too vague. Like, "The [REDACTED] radio [REDACTED] market." wouldn't make you think of anything, but "The [REDACTED] specimen proceeded to systematically take apart the radio and reassemble it into [REDACTED]. Due to [REDACTED] the nearby market at [REDACTED] evacuated and destroyed."

I think I've put across what I'm getting at- I don't seem to be very good with my words at the moment. But it otherwise does show promise. If/when you do start tightening it up, I would recommend elaborating on the 'monsters' before anything and making the capabilities of the 'maze' a bit more solid- it says that you can't go through the plants or jump over the hedges, but the censored parts just seem to come across as "You just can't, okay? Forget it." Even elaborating on the 'hidden entrance' would be welcome.

You still want to be vague, but not too vague.







